= Valentín Campa

*Corriente: los ortodoxos. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

He walked out of Lecumberri after eleven years the way other men walk out of an office that owes them nothing. Ferrocarrilero since the twenties, expelled from the Party once for refusing to organize the killing of Trotsky — an anecdote he does not tell, which everyone knows — and back in it because there was never really anywhere else.

He does not talk about the prison. He talks about the railway workers' pension tables, which he has kept in his head, updated, for eleven years.

